@startuml fig-l2-l3-changes
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title L2 Addresses Change per Hop — L3 Addresses Remain End-to-End

participant "Host S\nIP: IP_S\nMAC: MAC_S" as S #FFE0B2
participant "Router R1\nMAC: R1a / R1b" as R1 #C8E6C9
participant "Router R2\nMAC: R2a / R2b" as R2 #C8E6C9
participant "Host D\nIP: IP_D\nMAC: MAC_D" as D #FFE0B2

S -> R1 : **L2:** MAC_S → MAC_R1a\n**L3:** IP_S → IP_D\nTTL = 64
R1 -> R2 : **L2:** MAC_R1b → MAC_R2a\n**L3:** IP_S → IP_D\nTTL = 63
R2 -> D : **L2:** MAC_R2b → MAC_D\n**L3:** IP_S → IP_D\nTTL = 62

legend right
  Source and destination IP remain the same
  across every hop (end-to-end principle).
  Source and destination MAC change at
  each router (next-hop L2 rewrite).
  TTL / Hop Limit decreases by one at each hop.
endlegend
@enduml
